
---


@startuml

' Classes
class Bus {
  +String id
  +String type
}

class Trajectory {
  +String id
  +String name
  +String description
  +Status status
  +Date submissionDate
  +Date approvalDate
  +List<Modification> modifications
}

class Line {
  +String lineNo
  +String name
  +Category category
  +List<Trajectory> trajectories
}

class Modification {
  +Date date
  +String description
  +Trajectory trajectory
}

class ApprovalRequest {
  +Date requestDate
  +ApprovalResult result
  +Trajectory trajectory
}

enum ApprovalResult {
  APPROVED
  REJECTED
  MODIFIED
}

enum Status {
  PENDING_APPROVAL
  APPROVED
  OPERATIONAL
  SUSPENDED
  CANCELLED
}

class MENSO_Ticket {
  +String cardNumber
  +Date startDate
  +Date endDate
  +Customer customer
}

class Trip {
  +DateTime timestamp
  +Line line
  +MENSO_Ticket mensoTicket
}

class Customer {
  +String id
  +String name
  +String homeAddress
  +String officeAddress
  +WorkingHours workingHours
  +MENSO_Ticket mensoTicket
}

class WorkingHours {
  +Day day
  +Time startTime
  +Time endTime
}

enum Day {
  MONDAY
  TUESDAY
  WEDNESDAY
  THURSDAY
  FRIDAY
  SATURDAY
  SUNDAY
}

class Invoice {
  +String id
  +Date issueDate
  +Date dueDate
  +BigDecimal amount
  +BigDecimal discount
  +Customer customer
  +List<Trip> trips
  +Category category
}

class Category {
  +String code
  +String description
  +BigDecimal basePricePerTrip
}

' Associations
Bus --> Line : assigned to

Line --> "1..*" Trajectory : contains
Trajectory --> "0..1" ApprovalRequest : has
Trajectory --> "0..*" Modification : has
Trajectory --> "1" Status : has state

ApprovalRequest --> "1" ApprovalResult : result is

MENSO_Ticket --> "1" Customer : belongs to
MENSO_Ticket --> "1" Category : category of line
Trip --> "1" MENSO_Ticket : recorded by
Trip --> "1" Line : traveled on

Customer --> "0..1" WorkingHours : provides
Customer --> "1" Invoice : receives
Invoice --> "0..*" Trip : includes
Invoice --> "1" Category : based on category
Category --> "1..*" Line : assigned to lines

@enduml

---

### 🧩 Explanation of Key Relationships

- **`Trajectory`** can go through multiple **approval requests**, each with a result.
- A **`Line`** may include multiple **trajectories**, especially during different times or variations.
- A **`MENSO Ticket`** is tied to a **`Customer`** and a **`Category`**, which affects pricing.
- **`Trip`** records are collected for invoicing and analyzing behavior.
- **`Invoice`** is generated per month, including all trips and applying discounts if applicable.
- **`WorkingHours`** help De Lijn understand when customers are likely to travel.

